{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"lists-and-tables\"><a href=\"#lists-and-tables\" aria-label=\"lists and tables permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Lists and tables</h1>\n<p>PatternFly offers two components for displaying large data sets: the data list and the data table. While they satisfy similar use cases, choosing the correct component to use in your design will be dependent on the type of data you need to display.</p>\n<p>Use <a href=\"#data-lists\">data lists</a> when:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A flexible layout is more important than arranging information in a grid</li>\n<li>You want to include active content like a chart</li>\n<li>Content displayed may vary between rows</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Use a <a href=\"#data-tables\">data table</a> when:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Users will want to consume data as a grid (i.e. structured rows and columns)</li>\n<li>You want column headers</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"data-lists\"><a href=\"#data-lists\" aria-label=\"data lists permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Data lists</h2>\n<p>PatternFly supports several variations of the data list component.</p>\n<h3 id=\"standard-data-list\"><a href=\"#standard-data-list\" aria-label=\"standard data list permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Standard data list</h3>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/v4/static/05688d6fc1e61bcfce273f115ffacd3b/1bb73/standard-list.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 700px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 74.44168734491315%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"standard data list\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/v4/static/05688d6fc1e61bcfce273f115ffacd3b/a8200/standard-list.png\"\n        srcset=\"/v4/static/05688d6fc1e61bcfce273f115ffacd3b/52d5c/standard-list.png 175w,\n/v4/static/05688d6fc1e61bcfce273f115ffacd3b/1bae2/standard-list.png 350w,\n/v4/static/05688d6fc1e61bcfce273f115ffacd3b/a8200/standard-list.png 700w,\n/v4/static/05688d6fc1e61bcfce273f115ffacd3b/0ab52/standard-list.png 1050w,\n/v4/static/05688d6fc1e61bcfce273f115ffacd3b/1bb73/standard-list.png 1209w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong><a href=\"../toolbar/design.md\">Toolbar</a></strong>: The toolbar sits above the list and contains controls for manipulating list data. Common actions include filtering, sorting, and pagination.</li>\n<li><strong>Row</strong>: Row height may be variable and sizes to the content. Rows in a data list may take any supported layout.</li>\n<li><strong>Inline actions</strong>: These actions apply only to the current row/item.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4 id=\"when-to-use\"><a href=\"#when-to-use\" aria-label=\"when to use permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When to use</h4>\n<p>Use a data list when the information you want to display is not easily structured into a tabular format, you want a more flexible layout within rows, or you plan to embed rich content like a chart or an image into a row.</p>\n<h4 id=\"when-not-to-use\"><a href=\"#when-not-to-use\" aria-label=\"when not to use permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When not to use</h4>\n<p>The data list is not recommended for displaying content that is better presented in tabular format with well defined columns and headings. Instead, use a data table.</p>\n<h4 id=\"alternative-solutions\"><a href=\"#alternative-solutions\" aria-label=\"alternative solutions permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Alternative solutions</h4>\n<p>Alternative to a data list include <a href=\"#data-tables\">data tables</a> or card views. Card views and data lists have similar properties, but information in a card view is chunked into a grid of individual cards. In choosing between a data list and a card view, consider the type of data that will be displayed and the format that best suits that data. If you cannot easily fit all of the data that needs to be displayed into a card, a data list might be a better solution.</p>\n<h4 id=\"how-to-use\"><a href=\"#how-to-use\" aria-label=\"how to use permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to use</h4>\n<p>Think of each row in a data list as a container for some formatted content. In PatternFly 4, data list rows can accept any <a href=\"/v4/documentation/react/layouts/bullseye\">layout</a> supported by the design system as long as all rows apply the same layout. Here are some common layouts that may be useful in a data list:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"/v4/documentation/react/layouts/grid\">Grid</a></strong>: when you want to display content in a responsive grid</li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"/v4/documentation/react/layouts/level\">Level</a></strong>: when you want to justify content evenly over the width of the row</li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"/v4/documentation/react/layouts/split\">Split</a></strong>: when you want to distribute content evenly with a main content area in the center</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"actionable-data-list\"><a href=\"#actionable-data-list\" aria-label=\"actionable data list permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Actionable data list</h3>\n<p>The actionable data list provides checkboxes that enable users to select one or more rows and act on that selection using options in the toolbar.</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/v4/static/292fb2063e23f6ba7218b0001a6af93d/1bb73/actionable-list.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 700px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 74.52440033085195%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"actionable data list\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/v4/static/292fb2063e23f6ba7218b0001a6af93d/a8200/actionable-list.png\"\n        srcset=\"/v4/static/292fb2063e23f6ba7218b0001a6af93d/52d5c/actionable-list.png 175w,\n/v4/static/292fb2063e23f6ba7218b0001a6af93d/1bae2/actionable-list.png 350w,\n/v4/static/292fb2063e23f6ba7218b0001a6af93d/a8200/actionable-list.png 700w,\n/v4/static/292fb2063e23f6ba7218b0001a6af93d/0ab52/actionable-list.png 1050w,\n/v4/static/292fb2063e23f6ba7218b0001a6af93d/1bb73/actionable-list.png 1209w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Checkbox</strong>: enables a user to select a row</li>\n<li><strong>Global actions</strong>: actions that can be applied to all selected items</li>\n</ol>\n<h4 id=\"when-to-use-1\"><a href=\"#when-to-use-1\" aria-label=\"when to use 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When to use</h4>\n<p>Use actionable data lists when you need to enable a user to select and act on multiple items in the list.</p>\n<h4 id=\"when-not-to-use-1\"><a href=\"#when-not-to-use-1\" aria-label=\"when not to use 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When not to use</h4>\n<p>Do not use actionable data lists when actions are restricted to a single row or object. In this case, place actions inline within the row.</p>\n<h3 id=\"expandable-data-list\"><a href=\"#expandable-data-list\" aria-label=\"expandable data list permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Expandable data list</h3>\n<p>The expandable list adds an expansion panel to every row to reveal more details about the item.</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/v4/static/ad76f3fd4d240a2b17bea0fc569266aa/1bb73/expandable-list.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 700px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 90.2398676592225%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"expandable data list\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/v4/static/ad76f3fd4d240a2b17bea0fc569266aa/a8200/expandable-list.png\"\n        srcset=\"/v4/static/ad76f3fd4d240a2b17bea0fc569266aa/52d5c/expandable-list.png 175w,\n/v4/static/ad76f3fd4d240a2b17bea0fc569266aa/1bae2/expandable-list.png 350w,\n/v4/static/ad76f3fd4d240a2b17bea0fc569266aa/a8200/expandable-list.png 700w,\n/v4/static/ad76f3fd4d240a2b17bea0fc569266aa/0ab52/expandable-list.png 1050w,\n/v4/static/ad76f3fd4d240a2b17bea0fc569266aa/1bb73/expandable-list.png 1209w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Expansion caret</strong>: toggles the expansion open and closed</li>\n<li><strong>Expansion panel</strong>: a container that is revealed when the expansion is open. It can accept any supported layout to present additional content to the user.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4 id=\"when-to-use-2\"><a href=\"#when-to-use-2\" aria-label=\"when to use 2 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When to use</h4>\n<p>Use an expandable data list when you have more information than will comfortably fit inside a row, or you want to provide a way for advanced users to access information that is not applicable to all users.</p>\n<h2 id=\"data-tables\"><a href=\"#data-tables\" aria-label=\"data tables permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Data tables</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Standard data table</strong>: combines the styling of a list view with behaviors that are commonly associated with a table (sometimes referred to as a hybrid list)</li>\n<li><strong>Compact data table</strong>: maximizes the amount of data that can be displayed in a small space</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"standard-data-table\"><a href=\"#standard-data-table\" aria-label=\"standard data table permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Standard data table</h3>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/v4/static/5d25aeca9fcb14fb96a7d02581444251/1bb73/standard-data-table.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 700px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 56.4929693961952%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"standard data table\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/v4/static/5d25aeca9fcb14fb96a7d02581444251/a8200/standard-data-table.png\"\n        srcset=\"/v4/static/5d25aeca9fcb14fb96a7d02581444251/52d5c/standard-data-table.png 175w,\n/v4/static/5d25aeca9fcb14fb96a7d02581444251/1bae2/standard-data-table.png 350w,\n/v4/static/5d25aeca9fcb14fb96a7d02581444251/a8200/standard-data-table.png 700w,\n/v4/static/5d25aeca9fcb14fb96a7d02581444251/0ab52/standard-data-table.png 1050w,\n/v4/static/5d25aeca9fcb14fb96a7d02581444251/1bb73/standard-data-table.png 1209w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong><a href=\"../toolbar/design.md\">Toolbar</a></strong>: sits above the list and contains controls for manipulating table data. Common actions include filtering, sorting, and pagination.</li>\n<li><strong>Select all</strong>: when present, selects all items in a table. If pagination is being used, this will only select items on the current page.</li>\n<li><strong>Column headers</strong>: should align with the content they contain. If the user is able to sort on a column, the first click on the header will sort the content of the table on the content in that column. Subsequent clicks will toggle the direction of the sort. Table data can only be sorted on one column at a time.</li>\n<li><strong>Select checkbox</strong>: selects this row</li>\n<li><strong>Global actions</strong>: actions that apply to all selected items</li>\n<li><strong>Inline actions:</strong> actions that apply only to the current row/item</li>\n<li><strong>Pagination footer:</strong> when present, provides navigation to additional pages</li>\n</ol>\n<h4 id=\"when-to-use-3\"><a href=\"#when-to-use-3\" aria-label=\"when to use 3 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When to use</h4>\n<p>Use a standard data table when the information you want to display fits into a structured, tabular format (i.e. has distinct rows and columns).</p>\n<h4 id=\"when-not-to-use-2\"><a href=\"#when-not-to-use-2\" aria-label=\"when not to use 2 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When not to use</h4>\n<p>Do not use for less structured or variably structured data that cannot be easily organized into columns. In these situations, use a <a href=\"#data-lists\">data list</a>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"how-to-use-1\"><a href=\"#how-to-use-1\" aria-label=\"how to use 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to use</h4>\n<p>Consider the structure of the data you want to display and organize that information into columns. Columns will typically have column headers. Every row within a table must have a consistent format. If the table row includes actions, they should always be placed in the rightmost column(s).</p>\n<h3 id=\"compact-data-table\"><a href=\"#compact-data-table\" aria-label=\"compact data table permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Compact data table</h3>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/v4/static/7a83ccf89ae187f4580c37f120d73334/1bb73/compact-data-table.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 700px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 37.220843672456574%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"compact data table\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/v4/static/7a83ccf89ae187f4580c37f120d73334/a8200/compact-data-table.png\"\n        srcset=\"/v4/static/7a83ccf89ae187f4580c37f120d73334/52d5c/compact-data-table.png 175w,\n/v4/static/7a83ccf89ae187f4580c37f120d73334/1bae2/compact-data-table.png 350w,\n/v4/static/7a83ccf89ae187f4580c37f120d73334/a8200/compact-data-table.png 700w,\n/v4/static/7a83ccf89ae187f4580c37f120d73334/0ab52/compact-data-table.png 1050w,\n/v4/static/7a83ccf89ae187f4580c37f120d73334/1bb73/compact-data-table.png 1209w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<h4 id=\"when-to-use-4\"><a href=\"#when-to-use-4\" aria-label=\"when to use 4 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When to use</h4>\n<p>Use a compact data table when you want to show as much data per page as possible and readability is a secondary concern.</p>\n<h3 id=\"expandable-data-table\"><a href=\"#expandable-data-table\" aria-label=\"expandable data table permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Expandable data table</h3>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/v4/static/9213bfc9ac6ab464f87ea803d5eb93ad/1bb73/expandable-data-table.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 700px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 78.90818858560795%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"expandable data table\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/v4/static/9213bfc9ac6ab464f87ea803d5eb93ad/a8200/expandable-data-table.png\"\n        srcset=\"/v4/static/9213bfc9ac6ab464f87ea803d5eb93ad/52d5c/expandable-data-table.png 175w,\n/v4/static/9213bfc9ac6ab464f87ea803d5eb93ad/1bae2/expandable-data-table.png 350w,\n/v4/static/9213bfc9ac6ab464f87ea803d5eb93ad/a8200/expandable-data-table.png 700w,\n/v4/static/9213bfc9ac6ab464f87ea803d5eb93ad/0ab52/expandable-data-table.png 1050w,\n/v4/static/9213bfc9ac6ab464f87ea803d5eb93ad/1bb73/expandable-data-table.png 1209w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Expansion:</strong> expands the row</li>\n<li><strong>Expansion panel:</strong> contains details associated with a row</li>\n</ol>\n<h4 id=\"when-to-use-5\"><a href=\"#when-to-use-5\" aria-label=\"when to use 5 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When to use</h4>\n<p>Use when you have more information than will comfortably fit inside a row or you want to provide a way for advanced users to access information that is not applicable to all users.</p>\n<h3 id=\"compound-expandable-data-table\"><a href=\"#compound-expandable-data-table\" aria-label=\"compound expandable data table permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Compound-expandable data table</h3>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/v4/static/840f5777bbd646b49fcf77c0c3e2b943/1bb73/compound-expandable-data-table.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 700px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 74.44168734491315%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"compound expandable data table\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/v4/static/840f5777bbd646b49fcf77c0c3e2b943/a8200/compound-expandable-data-table.png\"\n        srcset=\"/v4/static/840f5777bbd646b49fcf77c0c3e2b943/52d5c/compound-expandable-data-table.png 175w,\n/v4/static/840f5777bbd646b49fcf77c0c3e2b943/1bae2/compound-expandable-data-table.png 350w,\n/v4/static/840f5777bbd646b49fcf77c0c3e2b943/a8200/compound-expandable-data-table.png 700w,\n/v4/static/840f5777bbd646b49fcf77c0c3e2b943/0ab52/compound-expandable-data-table.png 1050w,\n/v4/static/840f5777bbd646b49fcf77c0c3e2b943/1bb73/compound-expandable-data-table.png 1209w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Expandable cell:</strong> a cell that can be clicked to reveal more detail about an item. If the expansion for an item is already open, clicking on a different cell will close the current item and open a new one.</li>\n<li><strong>Expansion panel:</strong> contains details associated with an expandable item.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4 id=\"when-to-use-6\"><a href=\"#when-to-use-6\" aria-label=\"when to use 6 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When to use</h4>\n<p>Use a compound expandable list when you want multiple expansion panels that relate to specific table columns where it would not make sense to combine all of this information into a single, simple expansion.</p>\n<h3 id=\"data-tables-on-mobile\"><a href=\"#data-tables-on-mobile\" aria-label=\"data tables on mobile permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Data tables on mobile</h3>\n<p>The PatternFly 4 data table is designed to be fully responsive. When columns no longer fit within the width of the viewport, columns are stacked so that data in each row is displayed as sets of attribute-value pairs.</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/v4/static/27b09ad4270fdf1848209bc969f96238/44727/Mobile-data-table-example.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 450px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 259.5555555555556%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"mobile data table\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/v4/static/27b09ad4270fdf1848209bc969f96238/44727/Mobile-data-table-example.png\"\n        srcset=\"/v4/static/27b09ad4270fdf1848209bc969f96238/52d5c/Mobile-data-table-example.png 175w,\n/v4/static/27b09ad4270fdf1848209bc969f96238/1bae2/Mobile-data-table-example.png 350w,\n/v4/static/27b09ad4270fdf1848209bc969f96238/44727/Mobile-data-table-example.png 450w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<h2 id=\"using-lists-and-tables-in-a-page\"><a href=\"#using-lists-and-tables-in-a-page\" aria-label=\"using lists and tables in a page permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Using lists and tables in a page</h2>\n<p>Lists or a tables should be placed in the body of a page. The width should be set by the containing element.</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/v4/static/bc55db16689ed5165cd3a0cf1e045888/8e846/data-table-example.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 700px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 70.26666666666667%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"table in a page\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/v4/static/bc55db16689ed5165cd3a0cf1e045888/a8200/data-table-example.png\"\n        srcset=\"/v4/static/bc55db16689ed5165cd3a0cf1e045888/52d5c/data-table-example.png 175w,\n/v4/static/bc55db16689ed5165cd3a0cf1e045888/1bae2/data-table-example.png 350w,\n/v4/static/bc55db16689ed5165cd3a0cf1e045888/a8200/data-table-example.png 700w,\n/v4/static/bc55db16689ed5165cd3a0cf1e045888/0ab52/data-table-example.png 1050w,\n/v4/static/bc55db16689ed5165cd3a0cf1e045888/fa92b/data-table-example.png 1400w,\n/v4/static/bc55db16689ed5165cd3a0cf1e045888/8e846/data-table-example.png 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>In this example, a data table is positioned in the body of a page in a card.</p>\n<h2 id=\"components-and-demos-used\"><a href=\"#components-and-demos-used\" aria-label=\"components and demos used permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Components and demos used</h2>\n<p><strong>HTML/CSS</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/v4/documentation/core/components/DataList\">DataList</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/v4/documentation/core/components/DataTable\">DataTable</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>React</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/v4/documentation/react/components/DataList\">DataList</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/v4/documentation/react/components/DataTable\">DataTable</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/lists-and-tables"}},"allGetStartedNavigationJson":{"edges":[{"node":{"text":"About","path":"/get-started/about"}},{"node":{"text":"Develop","path":"/get-started/developers"}},{"node":{"text":"Design","path":"/get-started/designers"}}]},"allDesignGuidelinesNavigationJson":{"edges":[{"node":{"text":"Styles","path":"/design-guidelines/styles/","subNav":[{"text":"Icons","path":"/design-guidelines/styles/icons"},{"text":"Typography","path":"/design-guidelines/styles/typography"}]}},{"node":{"text":"Usage and behavior","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/","subNav":[{"text":"About modal","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/about-modal"},{"text":"Alerts and notifications","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/alerts-and-notifications"},{"text":"Buttons and links","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/buttons-and-links"},{"text":"Data input","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/data-input"},{"text":"Empty state","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/empty-state"},{"text":"Filters","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/filters"},{"text":"Forms","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/forms"},{"text":"Lists and tables","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/lists-and-tables"},{"text":"Login","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/login"},{"text":"Modal","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/modal"},{"text":"Navigation system","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/navigation-system"},{"text":"Progress bar","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/progress-bar"},{"text":"Toolbar","path":"/design-guidelines/usage-and-behavior/toolbar"}]}},{"node":{"text":"Content","path":"/design-guidelines/content","subNav":[{"text":"Writing","path":"/design-guidelines/content/writing"},{"text":"Voice","path":"/design-guidelines/content/voice-and-tone"},{"text":"Style guide","path":"/design-guidelines/content/grammar-and-termin